Hierarchical Query: Used to query tree-structured data (e.g., employee/manager).
Keywords: START WITH, CONNECT BY PRIOR.
Partitioning: Dividing large tables into smaller pieces (partitions) while maintaining a single logical view.
Methods: Range (by date), List (by region), Hash (randomly distributed), and Composite (combination).
Bitmap Index: Uses bitstrings for indexing. Highly efficient for columns with low cardinality (few unique values, like Gender or Marital Status) and for complex AND/OR queries in data warehousing.


