1. General Collection Interfaces
The Java Collections Framework distinguishes between two main "branches":
The Collection hierarchy: Includes List, Set, and Queue.
The Map hierarchy: Represents key-value pairs.
[!IMPORTANT]
Is Map part of the Collection interface?
No. Although it is part of the Java Collections Framework, the Map interface does not extend the Collection interface. They are distinct because their data structures differ: Collection handles groups of individual objects, while Map handles pairs.
